# Extend NetworkPolicy to Layer 7
## Objective
This proposal extend NetworkPolicy to include Layer 7 attributes at both ingress and egress to extend filtering on HTTP method, HTTP path, Kafka topic, etc.

## Motivation
The current NetworkPolicy allows to apply security policies based on L3
and L4 information (pod to pod connectivity, pod to IP, port filtering). Many applications running in Kubernetes pods use modern protocols such as gRPC or REST to expose APIs. Securing such pods on pod and port level only provides limited security as the entire API is exposed. This proposal provides users the capability to lock down pods on API call level.

## Goals
* Provide a L7/API aware security specification compatible with NetworkPolicy
* The goal is to provide enforcement for:
   * Traffic that is coming from a pod (egress)
   * Traffic that is going to a pod (ingress)
* Find a simple language to express the most common use cases in locking down on L7/API level

## Non-Goals
* This proposal does not intent to capture L7 routing intent and is not a replacement for Ingress
* It is not the goal to provide capability to filter on every possible L7 protocol field.

## Implementation details

### API changes
We introduce a new field `Rules` on the existing `NetworkPolicyPort` structure which will contain rules for traffic passing through that port.

```go
// NetworkPolicyPort describes a port to allow traffic on
type NetworkPolicyPort struct {
	// The protocol (TCP or UDP) which traffic must match. If not specified, this
	// field defaults to TCP.
	// +optional
	Protocol *v1.Protocol `json:"protocol,omitempty" protobuf:"bytes,1,opt,name=protocol,casttype=k8s.io/api/core/v1.Protocol"`

	// The port on the given protocol. This can either be a numerical or named port on
	// a pod. If this field is not provided, this matches all port names and numbers.
	// +optional
	Port *intstr.IntOrString `json:"port,omitempty" protobuf:"bytes,2,opt,name=port"`

+	// The rule on the given port/protocol tuple. If this field is
+	// provided, the Port and Protocol field must be set as well and traffic will only be
+      // allowed when the traffic matches the provided rules.
+      // 
+      // +optional
+      Rules L7PortRule `json:"rules,omitempty" protobuf:"bytes,3,opt,name=application"`
}

// L7PortRule is a union of port level L7 rules. Mixing of different port
// level rule types is disallowed, so exactly one of the following must be set.
// If none are specified, then no additional port level rules are applied.
type PortRule struct {
	// HTTP specific rules.
	//
	// +optional
	HTTP []PortRuleHTTP `json:"http,omitempty" protobuf:"bytes,1,opt,name=http"`


         // Kafka specific rule.
         //
         // +optional
	Kafka []PortRuleKafka `json:”kafka,omitempty” protobuf:”bytes,2,opt,name=kafka”`
}
